properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 14 at 3:35PM PST until February 16 at 12:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow expected above 2500 feet. Total snow accumulations
of 6 to 14 inches.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains and valleys of Whatcom and Skagit
Counties, including the Mount Baker Ski Area, Cascade mountains
and valleys of Snohomish and King Counties, including Stevens
Pass, and Snoqualmie Pass and Cascade mountains and valleys of
Pierce and Lewis Counties, including the Crystal Mountain Ski
Area and Paradise on Mount Rainier.

* WHEN...From 6 AM Saturday to midnight PST Saturday night.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be difficult.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM SATURDAY TO MIDNIGHT PST SATURDAY NIGHT ABOVE 2500 FEET
